###Block: Regional Traits
# Andoran
# Ability Name		Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																			Required Region			Description																																																																																			Stackable?	Multiple?	Choose										Bonus to skill							Class Skill				Source Page		Aspects
Chainbreaker		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Chainbreaker],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran			DESC:You're an expert at rescuing slaves. You know that a few slaves freed from their chains can help turn the tide during a boarding action. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Disable Device checks made to open locks, Strength checks made to break chains or bars in order to free slaves, and combat maneuver checks made to sunder chains or bars in order to free slaves.																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Fight for Liberty		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Fight for Liberty],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]	PREREGION:Andoran			DESC:You inspire slaves to fight for freedom with a rousing battle cry. As a standard action, you  may make a rallying cry with a DC 15 Perform (oratory) check. On a successful check, any unarmed ally within 30 feet who is able to hear you gains a +2 trait bonus on attack rolls with improvised weapons and unarmed strikes. This bonus lasts for 1 round per level.																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Freedom Fighter		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Freedom Fighter],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran			DESC:You've developed a reputation as a privateer who fights for freedom. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Diplomacy checks. This bonus becomes a -2 penalty when dealing with slavers or those who support the slave trade. Diplomacy becomes a class skill for you.																																																									BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy|2|TYPE=Trait				CSKILL:Diplomacy			SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Pretend Pirate		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Pretend Pirate],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran			DESC:You enjoy luring slave ships to you. Sometimes you run a pirate flag to lull criminals into a false sense of security; other times you disguise yourself as a merchant ship. You gain a +2 bonus on Disguise checks made to disguise yourself as a pirate or merchant sailor. In addition, you can take 5 minutes to alter your ship's appearance to add +2 to the DC of any check made to identify your ship's allegiance or purpose.																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.5
# Mediogalti
Devilfish Diver		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait.SaveBonus	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Devilfish Diver],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Mediogalti		DESC:You've swum with the devilfish along the Mediogaltian coast. You gain a +2 trait bonus on saving throws versus poison.																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.7	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+2 trait bonus vs. posion
Dinosaur Whisperer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dinosaur Whisperer],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]	PREREGION:Mediogalti		DESC:After spending a month in the Mediogaltian jungle, you developed a knack for dealing with dinosaurs. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (nature) and Survival checks concerning dinosaurs. You also gain a +1 trait bonus on wild empathy checks made to affect dinosaurs.																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Pirate Duelist		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Pirate Duelist],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Mediogalti		DESC:You've rubbed elbows with pirates of all stripes in Ilizmagorti's taverns and convinced a few to show off their swordfighting skills. You gain a +1 trait bonus on attacks of opportunity made with daggers, short swords, cutlasses, rapiers, scimitars, or hook hands.																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Treasure Mapper		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Treasure Mapper],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Mediogalti		DESC:You've spent a great deal of time hunting down and following treasure maps - most false, but a few with legitimate information. You gain a +2 bonus on Survival or Profession (sailor) checks made to navigate using a map or chart, and one of them becomes a class skill for you.																																						STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Profession (Sailor)|Survival										CSKILL:LIST				SOURCEPAGE:p.7
# Okeno
Abolitionist Hunter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Abolitionist Hunter],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]	PREREGION:Katapesh		DESC:You hunt those who hunt slavers, whether as one of Captain Bhey's special task forces, or independently. You gain a +1 trait bonus on attack rolls when fighting abolitionists or those you have good reason to believe targeted you because of your slaver activities.																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.9
Cruel Master		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Cruel Master],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Katapesh		DESC:You're a master of dominating slaves through body language and inflection, and this ability carries over into other lines of work as well. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Intimidate checks, and it becomes a class skill for you.																																																													BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|2|TYPE=Trait				CSKILL:Intimidate			SOURCEPAGE:p.9
Slave Taker			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Slave Taker],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Katapesh		DESC:You specialize in disabling foes without wounding them, preserving their value as slaves. Whenever you deal nonlethal damage in combat, that damage increases by +1.																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.9
Whip Specialist		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Whip Specialist],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Katapesh		DESC:Your time spent lashing slaves has taught you how to get the most out of a whip. You deal +1 point of damage on all attacks made with a whip.																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.9
# Riddleport
Cyphermage Backer		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Cyphermage Backer],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]	PREREGION:Varisia			DESC:You've sold relics to a Cyphermage in the past, and she's agreed to assist you with future findings. When in Riddleport, you can use your contact to gain information about artifacts and history. Treat this ability as a single Knowledge (arcana) or Knowledge (history) check with a skill bonus of +15. You may make this check once per day that you spend in Riddleport. You can make a new check every day. Each time you do so, you can choose whether to use Knowledge (arcana) or Knowledge (history).																														SOURCEPAGE:p.11
Eager Combatant		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Eager Combatant],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Varisia			DESC:You're so excited to board other ships that you're frequently the first one over the rail, regardless of the danger. You gain a +1 trait bonus on attack rolls made while onboard an enemy ship.																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.11
Gold Goblin Regular	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Gold Goblin Regular],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]	PREREGION:Varisia			DESC:You're a frequent customer at the Gold Goblin Gambling Hall and enjoy some popularity within its walls. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Profession (gambler) checks anda +2 trait bonus on Diplomacy checks made to gather information when in Riddleport.																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.11
Shipboard Caster		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Shipboard Caster],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]	PREREGION:Varisia			DESC:You feel an affinity with ships and the sea, and the rolling rhythm of the waves helps focus your mind. When on a ship or other water-going vessel, you gain a +3 bonus on concentration checks.																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.11
# River Kingdoms
Expert Swimmer		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Expert Swimmer],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:River Kingdoms	DESC:Most pirates on the ocean view falling overboard as a death sentence, but in the River Kingdoms, it's often a key part of the strategy. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Swim checks, and it becomes a class skill for you.																																																															BONUS:SKILL|Swim|2|TYPE=Trait					CSKILL:Swim				SOURCEPAGE:p.13
Free Agent			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait.SaveBonus	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Free Agent],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:River Kingdoms	DESC:You embody the independent spirit of the River Kingdoms and do best when sailing under your own flag, in every sense. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Will saves to avoid charm and compulsion effects.																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.13	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+2 trait bonus on Will saves vs. charm and compulsion effects
River Navigator		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,River Navigator],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:River Kingdoms	DESC:You grew up in the River Kingdoms and are familiar with the many winding streams that cross the land. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Survival checks or Profession (sailor) checks dealing with lakes, rivers, and their immediate surroundings, and one of these skills becomes a class skill for you.																																			STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Profession (Sailor)|Survival	BONUS:SKILL|Profession (Sailor)|Survival|1|TYPE=Trait	CSKILL:LIST				SOURCEPAGE:p.13
River Sniper		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,River Sniper],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:River Kingdoms	DESC: Unlike seagoing pirates, you’re used to fighting most of your ship-to-ship battles at close range, and understand the value of a well-placed arrow. When on the deck of a waterborne vessel, you gain a +1 trait bonus on attacks with ranged weapons.																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.13
# The Shackles
Home Port			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Home Port],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:The Shackles		DESC:You have a fondness for a particular port, and the people who live and do business there return the sentiment. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Diplomacy checks to gather information in your chosen home port.																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.15
Hurricane Savvy		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Hurricane Savvy],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:The Shackles		DESC:You are used to sailing in the terrible winds that roll out from the Eye of Abendego, and can apply the skills you’ve learned to any storm. You treat wind effects as one wind force category less than they actually are, both for any personal checks you must make and for any you make to captain or steer a ship.																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.15
Narrow Escape		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Narrow Escape],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:The Shackles		DESC:You were captured by kuru cannibals and nearly devoured in a sacrificial ritual. At the last second you wriggled free from your bonds and escaped into the jungle. Your narrow escape has left you with a paranoid fear of capture. You secretly conduct regular sessions in which you slip out of different types of knots. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Escape Artist checks, and Escape Artist becomes a class skill for you.																													BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist|1|TYPE=Trait			CSKILL:Escape Artist		SOURCEPAGE:p.15
Ship Aptitude		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ship Aptitude],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:The Shackles		DESC:You are used to crewing on many of the different types of ships that sail the Shackles. As a result, you have a knack for quickly determining the weaknesses and strengths of any ship, even ones you’ve never set foot on before. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Profession (sailor) checks, and Profession (sailor) becomes a class skill for you.																																										BONUS:SKILL|Profession (Sailor)|1|TYPE=Trait		CSKILL:Profession (Sailor)	SOURCEPAGE:p.15

###Block: Religion Traits
# Besmara
# Ability Name			Category of Ability		Type					Multiple Requirements																		Description																																																																																						Source Page
Cheat Death (Besmara)		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.ReligionTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Cheat Death],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait]	DESC:Even Besmara's most faithful worshipers usually call upon her only in times of greatest need. Sometimes Besmara intervenes on behalf of her faithful; other times, she turns her face away as they sink beneath the waves. Once per day, when you would be reduced to 0 or fewer hit points as a result of a failed ability check, skill check, or saving throw on your part, you may invoke this ability in order to reroll the failed check. You must take the result of the second roll, even if it is worse than the original.	SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Expert Boarder (Besmara)	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.ReligionTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Expert Boarder],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait]	DESC:Besmara rewards those who board other vessels and take what they want. While fighting on the deck of a ship, you gain a +1 bonus on all attacks made with one-handed weapons.																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.27

